DEFENSIVE PATENT PLEDGE

Andrey Bubnov hereby pledges that, to the extent they hold any
patent claims covering the Synoema compiler, language specification,
or associated tooling, they will not assert such claims against any
party for making, using, selling, or distributing software that
implements the Synoema language specification or interoperates with
the Synoema compiler, UNLESS that party first asserts patent claims
against Synoema, its contributors, or its users.

This pledge is irrevocable and applies to all current and future
patent claims held by Andrey Bubnov related to:

1. BPE-aligned lexer design methodology — lexemes engineered to
   align with BPE tokenizer boundaries (e.g., GPT-4 cl100k_base,
   Claude) so that each language operator occupies exactly one token.

2. Intent-Bridging Annotation (IBA) system — the @? (informal),
   @! (contract), and @!! (formal proof) annotation mechanism used
   by LLMs during code generation but erased at compile time.

3. Automatic constrained-decoding grammar generation from language
   specifications — generating GBNF grammars from typed EBNF specs
   for use in SGLang/vLLM constrained decoding pipelines.

4. Context-window-optimized module interface generation — the .snm
   module interface format designed to fit within LLM context-window
   budgets (< 2KB per module).

This pledge does not extend to implementations that are not
substantially derived from or interoperable with Synoema.

This pledge is made in the spirit of the Open Patent Pledge and is
intended to foster innovation and interoperability in the programming
language and LLM tooling ecosystem.

Effective date: 2025-04-03
